# transient: a linear ramp from start to end over `duration` seconds. At tickrate
# 10, duration=1 s = 10 ticks; start=0, end=0.5 -> output rises 0.05/tick. phase
# runs 0->1; endoftransient goes high (and stays) when the end is reached.
# Output = start at t0 (no advance on the starting tick).
tickrate 10
patch <<<
[transient]
    start          = 0
    end            = 0.5
    duration       = 1
    output         = O1
    phase          = O2
    endoftransient = O3
>>>
@0 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@0 expect O2 0 tol 1e-4
@0 expect O3 0
@1 expect O1 0.05 tol 1e-4
@1 expect O2 0.1 tol 1e-4
@5 expect O1 0.25 tol 1e-4
@5 expect O2 0.5 tol 1e-4
@9 expect O1 0.45 tol 1e-4
@10 expect O1 0.5 tol 1e-4
@10 expect O2 1.0 tol 1e-4
@10 expect O3 1
@11 expect O1 0.5 tol 1e-4
@11 expect O3 1
